 der die überkommenen Macht- und Eigentumsverhältnisse bewahren will.  aThe volume compiles shorter works by the political philosopher Edmund Burke that reflect both his liberal and conservative tendencies. They help to correct the one-sided image of Burke as an anti-progressive critic of the French Revolution, and clearly demonstrate the relevance of his arguments for the current debate on the relationship between political elites and the electorate, on global justice, and on the future of conservatism.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aGerechtigkeit. 4aGlobalisierung. 4aKonservativismus. 4aPolitik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  aJustice.  aconservatism.  aglobalization.  apolitics.1 aAsbach, Olaf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAsbach, Olaf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBurke, Edmund, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJörke, Dirk, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJörke, Dirk, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2019 Part 1z978311076246408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2019z9783110606423oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103798390 cprintz978305004492740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978305008777140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783050087771423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783050087771/original  a978-3-11-071956-7  DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-076246-4  DG Plus DeG Packag